  "body": "I am working on a tree-like visualization where child nodes are nested inside their parent node. \nAs I expand the tree I hit the depth limit set by `MAX_TREE_DEPTH` from [ReactInstanceHandles.js](https://github.com/facebook/react/blob/dea7efbe16596bbab7965331e277de113aeaff27/src/core/ReactInstanceHandles.js#L25), getting the following error message:\n\n``` javascript\n'traverseParentPath(%s, %s, ...): Detected an infinite loop while ' + 'traversing the React DOM ID tree. This may be due to malformed IDs: %s',\n```\n\nI was wondering if you guys have plans to make the depth limit configurable. Is there any way to bypass this limitation?\n",
